sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: ASML stock rises after Bernstein upgrade; DRAM upcycle thesis back in play ahead of earnings

feed.title: Bernstein upgrades ASML stock rating to Outperform on DRAM cycle benefits
feed.summary: Bernstein SocGen Group upgraded ASML Holding NV from Market Perform to Outperform, significantly raising its price target to EUR1,300.00 from EUR800.00. This upgrade is driven by anticipation of a DRAM super cycle benefiting ASML, with major DRAM manufacturers expanding greenfield capacity and accelerating node migration, increasing demand for ASML's lithography equipment. Additionally, advanced logic expansion by TSMC for AI demand is expected to further boost ASML's growth, leading Bernstein to project an 18% EPS CAGR for ASML through 2025-27, surpassing consensus estimates.

feed.title: ASML Stock In The Spotlight Following An Analyst U-Turn — Here’s What’s Driving The Double Upgrade
feed.summary: Aletheia Capital analyst Warren Lau dramatically upgraded ASML Holding (ASML) stock from "Sell" to "Buy" and doubled its price target to $1,500 due to revised fiscal 2026 and 2027 earnings estimates. The upgrade is driven by anticipated higher demand for extreme ultraviolet lithography from DRAM suppliers, resilient deep ultraviolet orders from China, and a potential surge in TSMC demand. This optimistic outlook comes despite ongoing concerns about China's push for domestic chip equipment and ASML's expected decline in Chinese net sales in 2026.
